The son of a police sergeant in Delta State has been stabbed to death by his 13-year-old friend over financial disagreement, it was learnt. The Nation gathered that the incident happened Saturday night at the police quarters located behind the Ughelli office of the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC). The victim, Marvellous Ekrake, 15, was said to have bled to death from the wound he sustained. He was said to have collapsed at a neighbourâ€™s veranda where he struggled to for help. An eyewitness said a disagreement ensued between Ekrake and his friend Progress Life over how to share money for a job they both executed. When Marvellous refused to hand over a certain amount of money demanded, Progress picked up a kitchen knife and stabbed him in the throat and fled, the witness said.